rComments: Go to class you won't be disappointed!  His lecture slides are really basic so take note of what he says because that is where you will get the details for the midterm/final.

I really liked Neil as a lecturer, sometimes could skip through material a little fast, but he explains concepts well and is really funny and enjoyable to listen to. Definitely enjoyed his lectures, and it is easy to do well if you pay attention and take good notes. His slides aren't super detailed, so you'll definitely want to go to class!

Neil is a great prof. He explains concepts in a way thats clear and concise and also gives helpful examples.  Neil's examinations are based on what he teaches and emphasizes in class and he grades fairly.  However, I found Neil wasn't always available for questions after class and he was anxious to leave right after the lectures.
